(9, '799457-3255847', 'The Socialite', 'If what you love to do at <I>The Great Burlesque Exposition</I> is see the shows, hit the parties, and shop, than this is the combo package for you!\r\n\r\n<I>The Socialite</I> includes:\r\n<UL>\r\n<LI> One ticket to <B>The Rhinestone Revue</b> on Friday, Feb. 8\r\n<LI> One ticket to <B>The Burlesque Bordello</b> on Friday, Feb. 8\r\n<LI> One ticket to <B>The Main Event </b> on Saturday, Feb. 9\r\n<LI> One ticket to <B>The Pool Party</b> on Saturday, Feb. 9\r\n<LI> One ticket to <B>Miss Mina''s Tea</b> on Sunday, Feb. 10\r\n<LI> One ticket to <B>The Sunday Showcase</b> on Sunday, Feb. 10\r\n<LI>Plus everything in the <B>Fan Admission</B>\r\n<uL><BR><li><b>The Drop-In Classes:</B> Taught by instructors from <a href=http://www.StudyBurlesque.com>The Boston Academy of Burlesque Education</a>, drop-in classes teach all the burlesque basics. Each of the three 30-minute classes covers different subject matter: <i>Burlesque Bumps ''n'' Grinds</I>; <i>Keeping the Tease in Striptease</I>; and <i>Beautiful Boas</I> plus there''s a special sampler class at 7:00 p.m. for your pre-show entertainment! Classes are taught every hour on the hour from 1:00 p.m. to 7:00 p.m. on both Saturday, February 21 and Sunday, February 22. <i>Please note that The Drop-in Classes are <u>not</u> the same thing as The Conference or The Master Classes, both which require a separate registration fee.</i></li><BR><li> <b>Meet The Legends</B> <i>Saturday, noon to 1:00 p.m.</I>: Our special guest stars share the secrets of burlesque, both "back in the day" and what it''s like today!</LI><BR><li> <b>The Costume Exhibit</B> <i>Saturday & Sunday, noon to 8:00 p.m.</I>: You can''t take it off until you put it on! Feast your eyes on the most gorgeous creations from around the world! Curated by Rhode Island''s own BettySioux Tailor, The Costume Exhibit features a mix of new and historic costumes.</LI><BR><li> <b>The Fashion Show</B> <i> Sunday, noon</I>: A perfect post-Valentine mix of romantic and racy! Plus you''ll be able to buy many of the fashions from the vendors!</LI><BR><li> <b>The Art Show</B> <i>Saturday & Sunday, noon to 8:00 p.m.</I>: Every year we present a creative collection of artwork inspired by the burlesque world, from drawings to photographs, to sculpture.</LI></UL>\r\n</ul>\r\n<I>Plus...</I> As we did last year, we are reserving the first four rows at <I>The Rhinestone Revue, The Main Event,</I> and <I>The Sunday Showcase</I> for our "Socialite" and "Whole Shebang" attendees!\r\n\r\n\r\nPurchased separately, these tickets would cost you over $200 -- and some of them can''t be bought at any price! But a <I>Socialite Passport</I> can cost you as little as $125.00!', 0, '175.00', '2014-08-23 18:57:56', 'scratch'),
(10, '799457-3255846', 'The Socialite', 'If what you love to do at <I>The Great Burlesque Exposition</I> is see the shows, hit the parties, and shop, than this is the combo package for you!\n\n<I>The Socialite</I> includes:\n<UL>\n<LI> One ticket to <B>The Rhinestone Revue</b> on Friday, Feb. 8\n<LI> One ticket to <B>The Burlesque Bordello</b> on Friday, Feb. 8\n<LI> One ticket to <B>The Main Event </b> on Saturday, Feb. 9\n<LI> One ticket to <B>The Pool Party</b> on Saturday, Feb. 9\n<LI> One ticket to <B>Miss Mina''s Tea</b> on Sunday, Feb. 10\n<LI> One ticket to <B>The Sunday Showcase</b> on Sunday, Feb. 10\n<LI>Plus everything in the <B>Fan Admission</B>\n<uL><BR><li><b>The Drop-In Classes:</B> Taught by instructors from <a href=http://www.StudyBurlesque.com>The Boston Academy of Burlesque Education</a>, drop-in classes teach all the burlesque basics. Each of the three 30-minute classes covers different subject matter: <i>Burlesque Bumps ''n'' Grinds</I>; <i>Keeping the Tease in Striptease</I>; and <i>Beautiful Boas</I> plus there''s a special sampler class at 7:00 p.m. for your pre-show entertainment! Classes are taught every hour on the hour from 1:00 p.m. to 7:00 p.m. on both Saturday, February 21 and Sunday, February 22. <i>Please note that The Drop-in Classes are <u>not</u> the same thing as The Conference or The Master Classes, both which require a separate registration fee.</i></li><BR><li> <b>Meet The Legends</B> <i>Saturday, noon to 1:00 p.m.</I>: Our special guest stars share the secrets of burlesque, both "back in the day" and what it''s like today!</LI><BR><li> <b>The Costume Exhibit</B> <i>Saturday & Sunday, noon to 8:00 p.m.</I>: You can''t take it off until you put it on! Feast your eyes on the most gorgeous creations from around the world! Curated by Rhode Island''s own BettySioux Tailor, The Costume Exhibit features a mix of new and historic costumes.</LI><BR><li> <b>The Fashion Show</B> <i> Sunday, noon</I>: A perfect post-Valentine mix of romantic and racy! Plus you''ll be able to buy many of the fashions from the vendors!</LI><BR><li> <b>The Art Show</B> <i>Saturday & Sunday, noon to 8:00 p.m.</I>: Every year we present a creative collection of artwork inspired by the burlesque world, from drawings to photographs, to sculpture.</LI></UL>\n</ul>\n<I>Plus...</I> As we did last year, we are reserving the first four rows at <I>The Rhinestone Revue, The Main Event,</I> and <I>The Sunday Showcase</I> for our "Socialite" and "Whole Shebang" attendees!\n\n\nPurchased separately, these tickets would cost you over $200 -- and some of them can''t be bought at any price! But a <I>Socialite Passport</I> can cost you as little as $125.00!', 0, '150.00', '2014-08-23 18:53:49', 'BPT Auto Import'),
